sql:
SELECT creator_name, birth_year, profile_picture
FROM creators
ORDER BY birth_year ASC;

SELECT COUNT(creator_id) AS num_creators
FROM creators
WHERE birth_year = 1990;

SELECT creator_id, COUNT(issue_id) AS total_issues_contributed
FROM creator_contributions
GROUP BY creator_id;

SELECT COUNT(creator_id) AS num_creators
FROM creators
WHERE birth_year = 1980;

SELECT creator_name, birth_year
FROM creators
ORDER BY birth_year ASC;

SELECT creator_name, COUNT(creator_id) AS num_creators
FROM creators
GROUP BY creator_name;

external_knowledge:
- The term "prolific creators" refers to creators who have made the most contributions; 
- "Genre" in this context is a category of creative works, such as fiction, non-fiction, comics, etc., which is identified by `genre_id = 1`;
- "Version number of contributions" indicates the iteration or update level of a contribution.

